03/10/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Economy and Finance Minister Nikos Christodoulakis presented the draft state budget for 2004 on Thursday (2 October). 
The document envisions a 6.2 per cent increase in revenues and a 6.9 per cent rise in public spending, compared with 2003. 
He added that the government wants to reduce the deficit to 1.2 per cent of GDP in 2004 from 1.4 per cent this year. 
Economic growth is forecast to reach 4.2 per cent next year. 
(ANA, MPA - 02/10/03)
